snippet.title: Getting started with Agent Developer Kit (ADK)
snippet.description: Building complex, production-ready AI agents, especially multi-modal or multi-agent systems, can be challenging. Introducing the Agent Developer Kit (ADK), a new open-source project from Google designed to simplify this process based on Google's internal experience. ADK provides a powerful, open foundation (model-agnostic, deployment-agnostic, interoperable) that makes agent development feel like software development, complete with native multi-modal streaming and easy local debugging via a built-in UI. Watch this playlist to learn how Agent Developer Kit (ADK) can help you in your developer projects.

snippet.title: Google Wallet Developer Livestreams
snippet.description:
Welcome to the official Google Wallet developer livestream playlist! Join us as we dive deep into the world of Google Wallet development. In these livestreams, we'll have engaging conversations with experts, unveil the latest features of the Google Wallet API, and showcase innovative ways to integrate them into your apps. Stay ahead of the curve and gain valuable insights to enhance your app development with Google Wallet.

What you can expect:

- In-depth discussions: We'll explore the intricacies of the Google Wallet API and discuss best practices for implementation.

- Exclusive interviews: Hear from special guests, including industry leaders and Googlers, who will share their insights and expertise.

- New feature reveals: Be the first to know about the latest additions to the Google Wallet API and learn how to leverage them to create compelling user experiences.

- Creative use cases: Discover innovative ways to use Google Wallet features to engage your users and enhance their digital interactions.

Save this playlist to stay up-to-date on the latest Google Wallet developments and unlock the full potential of your apps. Don't miss out on these valuable resources and the opportunity to connect with the Google Wallet developer community! Join us on this exciting journey and be a part of the future of digital payments with Google Wallet!

snippet.title: Google Pay DevBytes
snippet.description:
If you're looking to integrate Google Pay into your application, we've created a series of informative videos to guide you through the process. These videos will provide you with step-by-step instructions on how to implement exciting Google Pay features, such as the dynamic button API and Autofill, which can greatly enhance the user experience within your app.

Additionally, the videos will delve into best practices for testing your Google Pay integration, ensuring that it functions seamlessly for all users. We'll also cover troubleshooting techniques, equipping you with the knowledge to quickly identify and resolve any issues that may arise during the integration process. By the end of these videos, you'll have the expertise to confidently add Google Pay to your app and provide your users with a secure and convenient payment option.
